td-b450cb: Add DB integrity constraints for audit checksum and enums
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P1
Labels: review-finding, security, code-quality

Description:
What is wrong: audit migrations define checksum/action/outcome columns but do not enforce value integrity at the DB layer; malformed values can be inserted via raw SQL or future non-changeset code paths. File refs: app/priv/repo/migrations/20260303153000_create_audit_logs.exs:11, app/priv/repo/migrations/20260303153000_create_audit_logs.exs:12, app/priv/repo/migrations/20260303153000_create_audit_logs.exs:16, app/priv/repo/migrations/20260303153000_create_audit_logs.exs:22, app/priv/repo/migrations/20260303153100_create_audit_checkpoints.exs:11. Suggested fix: add CHECK constraints for 64-char lowercase hex checksums (including optional previous_checksum) and constrained action/outcome enums at migration level, then map constraints in schema changesets where applicable. Found by: Security, Code Quality, Codex Fresh Eyes.

Acceptance Criteria:
1) Migration adds DB CHECK constraints for audit_logs.checksum, audit_logs.previous_checksum (nullable), audit_checkpoints.checksum, and audit_logs.action/outcome allowed sets. 2) Invalid direct SQL inserts are rejected by PostgreSQL. 3) Tests cover at least one invalid insert per new constraint.

